{"id":14881439,"mediaExerciseId":"85198470-c529-4eea-854c-95b4c5f8b336","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612383,"groupTitle":"Concept Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":"14.4","sectionTitle":"The Weighted Average Cost of Capital","pageNumber":476,"solutions":[{"id":5979953,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"$a)$ The firm's weighted average cost of capital is calculated by multiplying the weights of equity, debt, and preferred stock by their respective costs.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/a57e3699e6e696912d1e1cd5196281dd/ffa6f050d4d9704bea822f629f8dddfd/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/a57e3699e6e696912d1e1cd5196281dd/ffa6f050d4d9704bea822f629f8dddfd/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"$b)$ Because the interest rate is tax-deductible, the cost of debt is multiplied by $(1 - T_c)$ to lessen its tax effect when calculating a firm's weighted average cost of capital.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/a57e3699e6e696912d1e1cd5196281dd/eed6f661aaeee835adced05a53b9259e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/a57e3699e6e696912d1e1cd5196281dd/eed6f661aaeee835adced05a53b9259e/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"$c)$ Whenever the project under consideration is much like the company's existing business operations, using the weighted average cost of capital as the discount rate to compute net present value is appropriate, it is because the company's risk level rises as it invests in various projects. \n\nThe higher the risk, the greater the expected return, and the greater the firm's weighted average cost of capital, this project should be accepted if the cash flows are discounted at the weighted average cost of capital and the net present value is positive.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":293,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/a57e3699e6e696912d1e1cd5196281dd/e10b45dbf3c8e60f8d818b3633c35e20/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":147,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/a57e3699e6e696912d1e1cd5196281dd/e10b45dbf3c8e60f8d818b3633c35e20/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"aa52abd2-c1bb-44f2-a33c-257ba52853c6","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881440,"exerciseName":"5","page":479,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"55724060-aae2-4788-b88a-8c98923d86c9","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-concept-questions-5-55724060-aae2-4788-b88a-8c98923d86c9"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881438,"exerciseName":"2","page":472,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"536c9ad9-4d4d-4b5a-a254-2d